This folder 'Tutorial_1' (for trial with all the input files like PMATRIX1.dat , population_neigh1.dat , ref1.gro and neighborhood1.dat) contains the following : 

1) 1000frames.xtc is a short test trajectory that has 1000 frames of GB1 protein system with 16 residues having a total of 136 particles. 

2) GNAP.sh contains the plumed command ( '/plumed driver --mf_xtc 1000frames.xtc --plumed plumed.dat' ) to  run the plumed for generating GNAP values for the given test trajectory.

3) neighbourhood1.dat contains line-by-line the particle ID's of the neighbourhood of the various particles.

4) plumed.dat is a plumed input script for calculating GNAP value for the test trajectory.

5) PMATRIX1.dat contains the projection matrix P (for all the particles) which projects out the non-affine component of the total displacement vector of all the particles' environment.

6) population_neigh1.dat contains line-by-line the population of the neighbourhood of the various particles.

7) ref1.gro is just the gro format file of the reference structure deleting the 1st two lines in the gro format-file.

8) COLVAR.png is a png file that is the plot of the GNAP values that would be generatd for the given test system.

The above files 3,5 and 6  are actually generated using pmat.c program which is made availabe in the folder named tutorial_2.


